As an intern, the New York Times reported, Namrata Hegde's only task was to make 120 fruit-leather "beetles" every day. She was told not to laugh or, for that matter, make any other noise. All of which would be bad enough had Hegde been paid. But she was an unpaid intern at a restaurant that charged $500-per-person for its dinner menu.
